WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:18.280
Iris Press Publishers, Humpty and His Family by Yulia Puchkova

00:18.280 --> 00:28.040
Chapter 1 Life in the Egg Hello, I'm an ostrich.

00:28.040 --> 00:37.920
I'm from Africa, I live in the grasslands, now I'm grown up, but I want to start my

00:37.920 --> 00:45.320
story from the very beginning, here it is.

00:45.320 --> 00:52.840
I'm sitting in an egg, it is big and I'm big too.

00:52.840 --> 00:58.840
I'm tired of sitting here, I want to get out.

00:58.840 --> 01:05.160
I hit the egg with my beak, but nothing happens.

01:05.160 --> 01:10.040
It is sometimes light and sometimes dark in the egg.

01:10.040 --> 01:13.560
When it is dark, I sleep.

01:13.560 --> 01:19.480
When it is light, I want to go out.

01:19.480 --> 01:22.480
Now it is very light.

01:22.480 --> 01:33.840
I hit the egg with my beak again, suddenly there is a small hole in the wall of the egg.

01:33.840 --> 01:40.200
I take my beak out of the hole and put my eye to it.

01:40.200 --> 01:43.360
I'm looking through the hole now.

01:43.360 --> 01:48.920
Wow, it's great there.

01:48.920 --> 01:59.200
I can see a lot of green grass, some green trees and bushes, there are different animals,

01:59.200 --> 02:02.560
they are walking in the grass.

02:02.560 --> 02:10.520
Some animals are eating the grass, some animals are eating the leaves.

02:10.520 --> 02:16.960
I can see a cheater, it is lying in the tall grass.

02:16.960 --> 02:31.120
It is hiding from a zebra, the cheater looks very hungry, oh no, it wants to eat the zebra.

02:31.120 --> 02:42.440
I look at the zebra, it is eating grass, it doesn't see the cheater, I'm very angry.

02:42.440 --> 02:54.400
I want to get out, I shake the egg, suddenly the egg starts rolling, it is rolling and

02:54.400 --> 03:00.800
rolling and I'm rolling too, bang.

03:00.800 --> 03:09.800
The egg hits the cheater on the back, the cheater jumps up, turns around and looks at me.

03:09.800 --> 03:20.760
Of course, it can't see me, it can see only the egg, it looks and looks and shows me it's

03:20.760 --> 03:27.000
big, ugly teeth, I'm afraid.

03:27.000 --> 03:36.680
I'm not looking at it now, I'm hiding inside the egg, I'm very quiet.

03:36.680 --> 03:46.560
The cheater smells the egg, sneezes and walks away.

03:46.560 --> 04:01.720
I turn the egg, I can see the zebra now, it is running away, oh no, somebody is rolling

04:01.720 --> 04:13.680
me back, but I know her, she is my mum, she is big and strong, she is very tall too.

04:13.680 --> 04:20.800
Now I'm at home again, there are three eggs around me, there is my brother and two sisters

04:20.800 --> 04:27.960
inside them, it is dark now, I can hear my dad.

04:27.960 --> 04:37.280
He comes home every evening, he helps my mum a lot, he sits on the nest at night,

04:37.280 --> 04:53.640
now dad is sitting down on the nest, it is very dark, I'm tired and I sleep.

04:54.640 --> 05:07.600
There are two others, I wake up and open my eyes, it is light again, I look through the

05:07.600 --> 05:17.080
hole and see another egg, there is a hole in that egg too, there is an eye in the hole,

05:17.080 --> 05:27.720
they are looking at each other, now the eye winks at me, I wink too, I shake the egg

05:27.720 --> 05:35.880
and it starts rolling, my brother does the same, I'm rolling to my brother and he is

05:35.880 --> 05:46.000
rolling to me, there is a terrible noise, the eggs are a lot of white pieces now and

05:46.000 --> 05:53.880
we are out, we are free, we are lying on the grass, I put up my beak and say it to my

05:53.880 --> 06:10.240
brother, hello, hello he answers, our daddy is next to us, hi sons he says, let's give

06:10.240 --> 06:21.280
you names, he turns away and cries, dear come here, we've got two sons, we must give

06:21.280 --> 06:31.080
them names, this is the first time I can see our mother in the light, she is big and strong

06:31.080 --> 06:40.920
like our father, she is beautiful too, she looks at us, winks at our dad and says, let's

06:40.920 --> 06:53.320
call them Humpty and Dumpty, okay, says dad, but who is Humpty, our mum looks at us again,

06:53.320 --> 07:04.440
he thinks and says, let's ask them, so which of you is Humpty, me we answer together, no

07:04.440 --> 07:16.520
says our mum, only one can be Humpty, then I am Dumpty, we say together, my dear says mum,

07:16.520 --> 07:27.000
we have got a problem with their names, but we have got very good sons, okay, you are Humpty,

07:27.000 --> 07:38.720
she points at me and you are Dumpty, she points at my brother, now meet each other, says dad, hello,

07:39.200 --> 07:48.800
I say to my brother, I'm Humpty, nice to meet you, he says, I'm Dumpty, nice to meet you too,

07:48.800 --> 07:56.320
I say and we shake wings, good chicks say our parents and smile,

07:56.320 --> 08:16.920
chapter three, naughty legs, Dumpty and I are lying on the grass, dad is looking at us,

08:17.720 --> 08:34.000
it's time to get up, he says, I get up, now I'm standing, but my legs don't want to stand, they are shaking, I fall down on the grass,

08:34.720 --> 09:02.640
Dumpty is laughing, it's your turn now says dad, Dumpty stops laughing, now he gets up, but his legs are like mine, they start shaking and he falls down too, he's laughing again, why are you laughing, asks dad, you can't walk?

09:02.640 --> 09:05.720
It isn't funny.

09:05.720 --> 09:08.960
But my legs don't listen to me, laughs dumpty.

09:08.960 --> 09:15.160
Of course they don't, they haven't got any ears, I say, to dumpty.

09:15.160 --> 09:19.600
Dad looks at me, then, at his legs.

09:19.600 --> 09:25.480
I haven't got any ears on my legs, but I can walk, he says.

09:25.480 --> 09:27.380
It is interesting.

09:27.380 --> 09:29.920
I think, and think.

09:29.920 --> 09:33.880
Suddenly, I have an idea.

09:33.880 --> 09:37.600
It is because you listen to your legs, I say.

09:37.600 --> 09:40.640
You walk when they want to walk.

09:40.640 --> 09:44.720
Mmm, says Dad.

09:44.720 --> 09:46.320
What about your legs?

09:46.320 --> 09:50.240
Don't they want to walk?

09:50.240 --> 09:53.440
Dumpty and I listen to our legs.

09:53.440 --> 09:56.560
No, they don't.

09:56.560 --> 09:58.720
We say together.

09:58.720 --> 10:02.800
But there are a lot of angry animals around us.

10:02.800 --> 10:07.720
If you can't run, they can catch and eat you.

10:07.720 --> 10:09.440
How can they do it?

10:09.440 --> 10:10.880
Asks dumpty.

10:10.880 --> 10:14.720
You are always with us.

10:14.720 --> 10:18.680
Sometimes I sleep, says Dad.

10:18.680 --> 10:21.480
Then there is mum, I say.

10:21.480 --> 10:26.520
She sometimes sleeps too, says Dad.

10:26.520 --> 10:37.880
You can always do it in turn, we say together.

10:37.880 --> 10:42.960
Chapter four, an ungrateful animal.

10:42.960 --> 10:46.040
It is a great day today.

10:46.040 --> 10:49.120
Dumpties and my legs want to walk.

10:49.120 --> 10:50.920
They like it.

10:50.920 --> 10:53.360
They start running.

10:53.360 --> 10:58.080
We always fall down.

10:58.080 --> 11:01.080
Dad and mum are happy.

11:01.080 --> 11:05.840
They are looking at us and smiling.

11:05.840 --> 11:08.040
I start running again.

11:08.040 --> 11:11.720
Suddenly, I can see a zebra.

11:11.720 --> 11:14.120
I look and look.

11:14.120 --> 11:15.320
I know it.

11:15.320 --> 11:17.080
It is my zebra.

11:17.080 --> 11:19.920
I run to it.

11:19.920 --> 11:22.160
Hello, I say.

11:22.160 --> 11:25.520
I know you, but you don't know me.

11:25.520 --> 11:28.320
I'm humpty.

11:28.320 --> 11:34.320
The zebra looks at me and says, but I don't want to know you.

11:34.320 --> 11:39.120
Why, I ask.

11:39.120 --> 11:49.400
It is because we, zebras, are beautiful, clever animals, and you, ostriches, are ugly, silly

11:49.400 --> 11:52.640
words.

11:52.640 --> 11:54.960
Suddenly I can see dumpties.

11:54.960 --> 11:56.960
He is next to me now.

11:56.960 --> 12:00.520
You can hear the zebra's words too.

12:00.520 --> 12:07.880
First, clever animals don't say bad things about other animals.

12:07.880 --> 12:10.320
Second, you aren't beautiful.

12:10.320 --> 12:17.560
You've got a short, thick neck, says he, and no feathers, I say.

12:17.560 --> 12:21.200
The zebra is angry.

12:21.200 --> 12:27.400
It wants to hit us, and it runs at us.

12:27.400 --> 12:29.160
What is it?

12:29.160 --> 12:31.440
Our legs want to run too.

12:31.440 --> 12:35.640
Now, we are running very fast.

12:35.640 --> 12:42.640
Suddenly, our legs turn left, and the zebra turns left too.

12:42.640 --> 12:45.880
It almost falls.

12:45.880 --> 12:52.720
When our legs turn right, the zebra can't turn so fast.

12:52.720 --> 12:54.960
It falls down on the ground.

12:54.960 --> 12:58.800
Its legs are up in the air.

12:58.800 --> 13:01.920
We ask, sorry, we can't help you.

13:01.920 --> 13:03.520
You're too heavy too.

13:03.520 --> 13:08.360
We cry to it and run away.

13:08.360 --> 13:10.360
We come to our parents.

13:10.440 --> 13:17.520
Dad, mum, we can run now, and when we are running very fast, we can certainly turn left

13:17.520 --> 13:20.040
or right.

13:20.040 --> 13:23.960
It is very good, say Dad and mum.

13:23.960 --> 13:26.040
Only ostriches can do that.

13:26.040 --> 13:28.760
Do you want to know our teacher?

13:28.760 --> 13:30.440
We ask.

13:30.440 --> 13:35.200
Yes, they say, who is it?

13:35.200 --> 13:47.360
It is that funny animal in a striped costume.

13:47.360 --> 13:50.400
Chapter 5.

13:50.400 --> 13:54.280
What a name.

13:54.280 --> 13:57.280
It is very hot today.

13:57.280 --> 14:03.000
Our parents are standing and we are lying on the grass.

14:03.000 --> 14:05.400
We are waiting for our sisters.

14:05.400 --> 14:09.960
They are still inside the eggs.

14:09.960 --> 14:12.240
Mum and Dad are worried.

14:12.240 --> 14:17.440
Our sisters must come out, but they don't.

14:17.440 --> 14:21.200
Can we help them, my brother and I ask?

14:21.200 --> 14:23.520
We can't help them, say Dad.

14:23.520 --> 14:25.800
They must do it themselves.

14:25.800 --> 14:32.000
I'm sure they are girls, say is dumpty.

14:32.000 --> 14:33.880
How do you know?

14:33.880 --> 14:34.880
Asks Dad.

14:34.880 --> 14:38.280
They are not strong.

14:38.280 --> 14:39.720
Answers my brother.

14:39.720 --> 14:43.080
Yes, they are weak, I say.

14:43.080 --> 14:44.880
We must help them.

14:44.880 --> 14:48.560
I'm sure they can't get out themselves.

14:48.560 --> 14:52.440
Suddenly, we can hear a noise.

14:52.440 --> 14:56.360
There are two holes in one of the eggs.

14:56.360 --> 15:01.440
I can see two beautiful brown eyes in the holes.

15:01.440 --> 15:03.200
They are looking at me.

15:03.200 --> 15:05.760
Hello, I say.

15:05.760 --> 15:07.560
I'm humpty.

15:07.560 --> 15:09.840
And who are you?

15:09.840 --> 15:13.360
Mmm, says the egg.

15:13.360 --> 15:16.160
Then there is a loud noise again.

15:16.160 --> 15:18.280
And there is no egg now.

15:18.280 --> 15:22.680
There is a beautiful chick in front of us.

15:22.680 --> 15:25.640
Of course, it is a girl.

15:25.640 --> 15:27.840
She is our sister.

15:27.840 --> 15:33.600
She has got very soft, long feathers and a long, sporty neck.

15:33.600 --> 15:38.680
Let's call her beauty, says Mum.

15:38.680 --> 15:42.320
No, says my sister.

15:42.320 --> 15:45.600
I don't like this name.

15:45.600 --> 15:48.400
What about feathery?

15:48.400 --> 15:50.160
Asks Dad.

15:50.160 --> 15:54.160
No, she says again.

15:54.160 --> 16:02.800
At this moment, we can hear a terrible noise, and our other sister comes out of the egg.

16:02.800 --> 16:06.160
She is very beautiful too.

16:06.160 --> 16:07.880
But she is small.

16:07.880 --> 16:10.120
She is smiling at us.

16:10.120 --> 16:13.280
A smile is so nice and kind.

16:13.280 --> 16:16.880
Hello, smiley, I say.

16:16.880 --> 16:19.760
Nice to meet you.

16:19.760 --> 16:23.320
And smiley, she cries and smiles again.

16:23.320 --> 16:25.040
I like it.

16:25.040 --> 16:27.280
It's a nice name.

16:27.280 --> 16:32.000
Good girl, says Mum, but we have a problem with your sister.

16:32.000 --> 16:36.040
We can't find a name for her.

16:36.040 --> 16:38.320
Let's ask her, says smiley.

16:38.320 --> 16:41.080
What's your name?

16:41.080 --> 16:49.080
Our big sister looks around and sees a very beautiful dragonfly.

16:49.080 --> 16:50.520
What is this?

16:50.520 --> 16:51.520
She asks.

16:51.520 --> 16:56.440
It's a dragonfly, says Mum.

16:56.440 --> 17:01.960
Then my name is dragonfly, says our sister.

17:01.960 --> 17:07.360
Oh, it's a very long name, says Dad.

17:07.360 --> 17:10.080
We must make it short.

17:10.080 --> 17:13.360
We can call you fly.

17:13.360 --> 17:17.640
Or dragon, says dumpty.

17:17.640 --> 17:22.960
Once I don't want to have a dragon in the family, cries Dad.

17:22.960 --> 17:28.960
And I want to be a dragon, says our sister, and stamps.

17:28.960 --> 17:33.160
Okay, says Mum.

17:33.160 --> 17:35.400
Be dragon if you like.

17:35.400 --> 17:46.800
And she winks at Dad.

17:46.800 --> 17:52.560
After six, strange grown-ups.

17:52.560 --> 17:57.360
Today we are going out into the world.

17:57.360 --> 18:01.600
It is the first time Dad and Mum take us with them.

18:01.600 --> 18:04.840
We walk together.

18:04.840 --> 18:09.480
Then we see two very big ostriches.

18:09.480 --> 18:12.120
They are walking too.

18:12.120 --> 18:14.960
They are coming to us.

18:15.040 --> 18:19.360
Now we can see three small chicks with them.

18:19.360 --> 18:22.880
They are all girls.

18:22.880 --> 18:25.400
Our parents stop.

18:25.400 --> 18:28.280
They talk to the big ostriches.

18:28.280 --> 18:32.720
They say, oh, what beautiful daughters you have got.

18:32.720 --> 18:41.520
Their necks are so long, their feathers are so soft, their beaks are so thick.

18:41.520 --> 18:48.720
The big ostriches smile and say, and your daughters are so cute.

18:48.720 --> 18:57.440
They've got long legs and small bodies, their smiles are so nice, and your sons are so strong,

18:57.440 --> 19:04.040
their eyes are so clever, their heads are so round.

19:04.040 --> 19:14.440
I look at my brother, at his eyes and head, and I say, that is not true.

19:14.440 --> 19:18.280
We can't be strong because we're very small.

19:18.280 --> 19:25.560
We can't be clever because we're very young, and our heads aren't round because they are

19:25.560 --> 19:27.040
square.

19:27.040 --> 19:30.560
Why do you say that?

19:30.560 --> 19:32.320
Dad is looking at me.

19:32.320 --> 19:37.520
I can feel that, and he is very angry.

19:37.520 --> 19:39.040
But why?

19:39.040 --> 19:48.200
I look at him and ask, Dad, why are you angry with me?

19:48.200 --> 19:52.320
Because you are rude, my son, he answers.

19:52.320 --> 19:54.920
Why am I rude?

19:54.920 --> 19:58.040
I don't know, he says.

19:58.040 --> 20:06.640
I think it is because you are too small, too young, and your head is too square.

20:06.640 --> 20:10.160
I don't understand my dad.

20:10.160 --> 20:21.920
Sometimes grown-ups are so strange.

20:21.920 --> 20:30.000
In Chapter 7, why does she run away?

20:30.000 --> 20:33.800
I'm hot and very thirsty.

20:33.800 --> 20:39.960
I come up to Dad and say, Dad, I'm hot and thirsty.

20:39.960 --> 20:42.480
Can we go and find water?

20:43.480 --> 20:52.480
Okay, says Dad, hide under my wings, and tell your brother and sisters to hide there, too.

20:52.480 --> 21:01.480
Hey, dumpty, smiley, dragon, come here, it's cool under Dad's wings, I cry.

21:01.480 --> 21:06.480
They run to us, and soon we're all together.

21:07.480 --> 21:12.480
Let's play, hide and seek, says dumpty.

21:12.480 --> 21:21.480
Let's, we say, humpty, you must look for us, says dragon.

21:21.480 --> 21:22.480
Why not?

21:22.480 --> 21:25.480
I close my eyes.

21:25.480 --> 21:31.480
It is very funny to hide in Dad's feathers or between his legs.

21:31.480 --> 21:36.480
First I find dumpty, then I find smiley.

21:36.480 --> 21:41.480
Oh, I can't find dragon, where is she?

21:41.480 --> 21:45.480
Suddenly, we can hear a small voice.

21:45.480 --> 21:49.480
Hello, can I play with you?

21:49.480 --> 21:53.480
We look and see a cute ostrich girl.

21:53.480 --> 21:57.480
I like her, and I say, of course you can.

21:57.480 --> 21:59.480
Can you help me?

21:59.480 --> 22:04.480
Yes, she says, and smiles, what must I do?

22:04.480 --> 22:08.480
We must find dragon, I answer.

22:08.480 --> 22:13.480
The girl starts shaking, then she cries.

22:13.480 --> 22:15.480
Mommy!

22:15.480 --> 22:19.480
And runs away.

22:19.480 --> 22:22.480
I look at dumpty and smiley.

22:22.480 --> 22:26.480
Why doesn't she want to find dragon, I ask?

22:26.480 --> 22:30.480
We don't know, they answer.

22:30.480 --> 22:36.480
Now we are looking for dragon together, but we can't find her.

22:36.480 --> 22:39.480
Suddenly, I can see dragon.

22:39.480 --> 22:44.480
She is running between mom's legs and laughing at us.

22:44.480 --> 22:49.480
I'm very clever, she cries.

22:49.480 --> 22:53.480
Soon, we come to a big river.

22:53.480 --> 22:58.480
There are a lot of animals next to the river.

22:58.480 --> 23:01.480
They are drinking water.

23:01.480 --> 23:06.480
There are antelopes, giraffes and elephants.

23:06.480 --> 23:09.480
They are big, but kind.

23:09.480 --> 23:12.480
There are lions too.

23:12.480 --> 23:16.480
Dad says they are angry.

23:16.480 --> 23:22.480
I look at dad, he isn't afraid of lions, he is very brave.

23:23.480 --> 23:27.480
We come up to the river and drink.

23:27.480 --> 23:31.480
The water is tasty and cool.

23:31.480 --> 23:36.480
I want to play with the water, I go into the river.

23:36.480 --> 23:44.480
Humpty, you mustn't wet your body, cries mom, only your legs.

23:44.480 --> 23:47.480
My legs are in the water now.

23:47.480 --> 23:51.480
Smiley is looking at me, she is afraid.

23:52.480 --> 23:55.480
Smiley, come here I cry.

23:55.480 --> 23:58.480
The water is soft and kind.

23:58.480 --> 24:01.480
My legs like it.

24:01.480 --> 24:05.480
Smiley goes into the water, she likes it.

24:05.480 --> 24:08.480
Dumpety is in the water too.

24:08.480 --> 24:12.480
Now all our legs are in the water.

24:12.480 --> 24:17.480
Suddenly, we can hear the small voice again.

24:17.480 --> 24:20.480
Can I play with you?

24:20.480 --> 24:25.480
I turn round and see that cute ostrich girl.

24:25.480 --> 24:28.480
I'm happy to see you again, I say.

24:28.480 --> 24:30.480
Let's play together.

24:30.480 --> 24:36.480
I'm Humpty, this is Smiley and that is Dumpty.

24:36.480 --> 24:38.480
Nice to meet you.

24:38.480 --> 24:44.480
I'm softy, says the girl and smiles.

24:45.480 --> 24:50.480
Wait, say Smiley, we can't start playing, we must call Dragon.

24:50.480 --> 24:52.480
Dragon, we cry.

24:52.480 --> 24:54.480
Dragon, come here.

24:54.480 --> 24:58.480
There she is, Dragon is running to us.

24:58.480 --> 25:01.480
Dragon, I say, we've got a friend.

25:01.480 --> 25:05.480
Her name is softy.

25:05.480 --> 25:10.480
I turn my head, but there is no softy.

25:10.480 --> 25:14.480
Where is your friend, asks Dragon.

25:14.480 --> 25:19.480
I don't know, I say and look around.

25:19.480 --> 25:22.480
Suddenly, I can see softy.

25:22.480 --> 25:27.480
She's running away, very fast.

25:27.480 --> 25:33.480
I'm very sad, I don't know why, but I like softy.

25:33.480 --> 25:37.480
I think she's very strange.

25:37.480 --> 25:44.480
First, she wants to play with us, but then she always runs away.

25:44.480 --> 25:46.480
Why?

25:53.480 --> 25:56.480
Chapter 8

25:56.480 --> 26:00.480
Living Stones

26:00.480 --> 26:04.480
We're standing with our legs in the river.

26:04.480 --> 26:08.480
Dragon is looking at the water.

26:08.480 --> 26:22.480
Suddenly, she says, look, there are big brown stones in the water.

26:22.480 --> 26:28.480
I look at the stones, they are very interesting.

26:28.480 --> 26:35.480
Dragon, have stones got eyes, I ask.

26:35.480 --> 26:39.480
Of course they haven't, she answers.

26:39.480 --> 26:49.480
Dragon, have stones got ears, I ask my second question.

26:49.480 --> 26:54.480
Of course they haven't, you are so silly, Humpty.

26:54.480 --> 27:03.480
Dragon, have stones got nostrils, I ask my third question.

27:03.480 --> 27:11.480
She looks at me, puts her wing to her head and turns it there three times.

27:11.480 --> 27:17.480
Then you aren't standing on a stone, I say.

27:17.480 --> 27:23.480
Because your stone is looking at me and listening to us

27:23.480 --> 27:28.480
and it has got a big nose.

27:28.480 --> 27:40.480
Ha ha ha, cries Dragon, you are too hot.

27:40.480 --> 27:45.480
Turn your head down and look, I say.

27:45.480 --> 27:50.480
Now, Dragon is looking at the stone under her toes

27:50.480 --> 27:56.480
and the stone is looking at her, their eyes meet.

27:56.480 --> 28:01.480
Dragon is afraid, she is shaking.

28:01.480 --> 28:11.480
Hello, she whispers, hmm, says the stone.

28:11.480 --> 28:15.480
Mummy!

28:16.480 --> 28:25.480
Cries Dragon and jumps off the stone.

28:25.480 --> 28:31.480
The stone starts growing, it grows and grows.

28:31.480 --> 28:38.480
Now it has got a fat body and a very big mouth.

28:38.480 --> 28:44.480
Hello, I'm a hippo, says the stone.

28:44.480 --> 28:48.480
And I'm Dragon, says my sister.

28:48.480 --> 28:54.480
Dragon asks the hippo and starts shaking.

28:54.480 --> 29:00.480
Oh, I'm so afraid, please don't eat me, Dragon.

29:00.480 --> 29:06.480
Now, he is laughing, but he looks very kind.

29:06.480 --> 29:12.480
I understand, he is playing with Dragon.

29:12.480 --> 29:18.480
Dragon is very angry, she thinks he is laughing at her.

29:18.480 --> 29:20.480
Let's go, chicks.

29:20.480 --> 29:26.480
She says to us, it's silly to talk to a stone.

29:26.480 --> 29:32.480
The hippo can hear her words, he stops laughing.

29:32.480 --> 29:38.480
Now, he looks sad, he says,

29:38.480 --> 29:42.480
that's why we live under water.

29:42.480 --> 29:48.480
And he goes under the water again.

29:48.480 --> 29:51.480
I feel very bad.

29:51.480 --> 30:03.480
My sister is sometimes so rude.

30:04.480 --> 30:08.480
Chapter 9

30:08.480 --> 30:13.480
They want to live too.

30:13.480 --> 30:17.480
I want to see Softie.

30:17.480 --> 30:21.480
I want to ask her why she always runs away.

30:21.480 --> 30:24.480
I look around.

30:24.480 --> 30:32.480
I can't see her in the river, I can't see her near the river.

30:32.480 --> 30:34.480
I'm very sad.

30:34.480 --> 30:39.480
Let's go home, says Mum.

30:39.480 --> 30:45.480
We get out of the water and walk home with Mum and Dad.

30:45.480 --> 30:51.480
Suddenly, a very small, green animal jumps at me.

30:51.480 --> 30:54.480
It is very funny.

30:54.480 --> 31:01.480
It has got four short legs and two very long and strong legs.

31:01.480 --> 31:05.480
It has got very big, funny eyes too.

31:05.480 --> 31:09.480
What's this? I ask Dad.

31:09.480 --> 31:11.480
It's food, he answers.

31:11.480 --> 31:13.480
Very tasty food.

31:13.480 --> 31:15.480
Eat it.

31:15.480 --> 31:18.480
I look at the animal.

31:18.480 --> 31:24.480
It is sitting on my left leg and making a funny noise.

31:24.480 --> 31:26.480
I can't eat it.

31:26.480 --> 31:30.480
I'm sure it wants to live.

31:30.480 --> 31:33.480
Suddenly, I can see a big beak.

31:33.480 --> 31:39.480
The beak opens and catches the animal.

31:39.480 --> 31:42.480
Oh no, I cry.

31:42.480 --> 31:44.480
I can see Dragon.

31:44.480 --> 31:48.480
The green animal is inside her beak.

31:48.480 --> 31:51.480
What are you doing, I cry?

31:51.480 --> 31:55.480
Open your beak.

31:55.480 --> 31:58.480
Answers Dragon.

31:58.480 --> 32:03.480
Then I take Dragon by the legs and shake her.

32:03.480 --> 32:09.480
Her beak opens and the green animal jumps out.

32:09.480 --> 32:14.480
Are you crazy, cries Dragon?

32:14.480 --> 32:18.480
I'm fine and you aren't kind, I say.

32:18.480 --> 32:24.480
Look, there are a lot of seeds and fruit in the grasslands.

32:24.480 --> 32:27.480
Why do you want to eat an animal?

32:27.480 --> 32:31.480
Because I like it, says Dragon.

32:31.480 --> 32:33.480
No, you don't.

32:33.480 --> 32:39.480
When you like somebody, you want to play with her or talk to her.

32:39.480 --> 32:43.480
You don't want to eat her.

32:43.480 --> 32:47.480
Laughs, Dragon.

32:47.480 --> 32:50.480
Humpty is in love.

32:50.480 --> 32:53.480
Dumpty, smiley, listen.

32:53.480 --> 32:56.480
Humpty is in love.

32:56.480 --> 32:58.480
Who is she?

32:58.480 --> 33:00.480
Tell us.

33:00.480 --> 33:05.480
Now, I am very angry.

33:05.480 --> 33:09.480
I want to hit Dragon, but I can't.

33:09.480 --> 33:12.480
She's a girl.

33:12.480 --> 33:15.480
Smiley looks at me.

33:15.480 --> 33:19.480
She understands me and she says,

33:19.480 --> 33:21.480
I'm in love too.

33:21.480 --> 33:25.480
It is so nice to be in love.

33:25.480 --> 33:28.480
My brother, Dumpty, looks at us.

33:28.480 --> 33:31.480
Then at Dragon and says,

33:31.480 --> 33:34.480
I'm in love too.

33:34.480 --> 33:38.480
That's a pity you are not, Dragon.

33:45.480 --> 33:47.480
Chapter 10.

33:47.480 --> 33:51.480
When we are together,

33:51.480 --> 33:56.480
today, Mum and Dad are at home,

33:56.480 --> 33:59.480
and we are not.

33:59.480 --> 34:02.480
We are walking and looking around.

34:02.480 --> 34:07.480
It is very interesting in the grasslands.

34:09.480 --> 34:12.480
I look at the grass.

34:12.480 --> 34:16.480
There are a lot of those green animals there.

34:16.480 --> 34:20.480
Mum says they are insects.

34:20.480 --> 34:25.480
My green animal's name is a grasshopper.

34:25.480 --> 34:28.480
There are other animals too.

34:28.480 --> 34:31.480
I can see ants.

34:31.480 --> 34:36.480
Butterflies, spiders and snails.

34:36.480 --> 34:38.480
Some grasshoppers are jumping.

34:38.480 --> 34:41.480
Some are singing.

34:41.480 --> 34:43.480
The ants are working.

34:43.480 --> 34:46.480
The butterflies are flying.

34:46.480 --> 34:48.480
The spiders are hunting.

34:48.480 --> 34:51.480
The snails are lazy.

34:51.480 --> 34:56.480
They are sleeping on the leaves or grass.

34:56.480 --> 35:02.480
Together we are watching insects and other animals.

35:02.480 --> 35:06.480
Only Dragon is not with us.

35:06.480 --> 35:09.480
She doesn't like watching small animals.

35:09.480 --> 35:12.480
She likes eating them.

35:12.480 --> 35:16.480
She can even eat a lizard.

35:16.480 --> 35:18.480
We are very quiet.

35:18.480 --> 35:23.480
A butterfly sits down on Smiley's wing.

35:23.480 --> 35:27.480
It is so beautiful.

35:27.480 --> 35:32.480
Suddenly, I can feel danger.

35:32.480 --> 35:36.480
We are watching a butterfly,

35:36.480 --> 35:40.480
and the lioness is watching us.

35:40.480 --> 35:45.480
Smiley, dumpty, I whisper.

35:45.480 --> 35:50.480
There is a lioness behind us.

35:50.480 --> 35:55.480
She is hiding in the bushes.

35:55.480 --> 35:57.480
They look at me.

35:57.480 --> 36:01.480
They are afraid.

36:01.480 --> 36:03.480
What can we do?

36:03.480 --> 36:06.480
They whisper to me.

36:06.480 --> 36:09.480
We must run very fast,

36:09.480 --> 36:12.480
and we must stay together.

36:12.480 --> 36:15.480
Now we are running,

36:15.480 --> 36:18.480
and the lioness is running after us.

36:18.480 --> 36:23.480
We can hear her behind us.

36:23.480 --> 36:25.480
Humpty, she can catch us,

36:25.480 --> 36:27.480
cries Smiley.

36:27.480 --> 36:30.480
Suddenly, I have an idea.

36:30.480 --> 36:33.480
Stop chicks, I cry.

36:33.480 --> 36:36.480
We must turn with our backs to each other,

36:36.480 --> 36:40.480
and stand in a circle, wing in wing.

36:40.480 --> 36:42.480
When the lioness jumps at you,

36:42.480 --> 36:44.480
you lie on the backs,

36:44.480 --> 36:47.480
and kick her with your legs.

36:47.480 --> 36:50.480
So, we stand in a circle.

36:50.480 --> 36:54.480
I can feel my brothers and sisters' backs behind.

36:54.480 --> 36:57.480
The lioness runs at me.

36:57.480 --> 37:00.480
Then she jumps at me.

37:00.480 --> 37:02.480
Now my friend backs,

37:02.480 --> 37:05.480
and give her a strong kick.

37:05.480 --> 37:07.480
The lioness flies away.

37:07.480 --> 37:11.480
Fly, lioness, fly.

37:11.480 --> 37:16.480
Now she is very angry.

37:16.480 --> 37:18.480
She is running around us.

37:18.480 --> 37:22.480
But every time, when she jumps at us,

37:22.480 --> 37:27.480
she gets a strong kick and flies away.

37:27.480 --> 37:30.480
The lioness comes back again.

37:30.480 --> 37:33.480
It is strange.

37:33.480 --> 37:37.480
I think she likes flying.

37:37.480 --> 37:40.480
At last, she is very tired.

37:40.480 --> 37:42.480
She can't catch us.

37:42.480 --> 37:47.480
She is still angry, but she walks away.

37:47.480 --> 37:49.480
Well done, Humpty,

37:49.480 --> 37:52.480
say my brother and sister.

37:52.480 --> 37:56.480
Well done, dumped in Smiley, I say.

37:56.480 --> 37:58.480
We are very proud today.

37:58.480 --> 38:02.480
We are only small, young ostriches.

38:02.480 --> 38:04.480
But when we are together,

38:04.480 --> 38:07.480
we can fight a lion.

38:14.480 --> 38:16.480
Chapter 11.

38:16.480 --> 38:19.480
A race.

38:19.480 --> 38:24.480
We are at home again.

38:24.480 --> 38:26.480
But we don't want to have a rest.

38:26.480 --> 38:29.480
We want to run and play.

38:29.480 --> 38:33.480
Dad looks at us, smiles and says,

38:33.480 --> 38:37.480
let's have a race.

38:37.480 --> 38:41.480
What is a race, I ask?

38:41.480 --> 38:46.480
It's when all the chicks run together to their mum.

38:46.480 --> 38:51.480
And one of them comes the first, says Dad.

38:51.480 --> 38:55.480
I want to be the first, says Dragon.

38:55.480 --> 38:59.480
I want to be the first, too, says Dumpty.

38:59.480 --> 39:02.480
And I can be the fourth, says Smiley.

39:02.480 --> 39:04.480
I don't want to be the first.

39:04.480 --> 39:08.480
And you, Humpty, asks Dad.

39:08.480 --> 39:10.480
I want to run.

39:10.480 --> 39:13.480
I like running, I answer.

39:13.480 --> 39:15.480
Then let's start,

39:15.480 --> 39:17.480
stand next to each other.

39:17.480 --> 39:22.480
One, two, three, go.

39:22.480 --> 39:25.480
We all start running to mum.

39:25.480 --> 39:29.480
She's standing very far away.

39:29.480 --> 39:32.480
Smiley is running the first.

39:32.480 --> 39:34.480
She's in front of me.

39:34.480 --> 39:37.480
I look behind and see Dumpty.

39:37.480 --> 39:40.480
He's the third.

39:40.480 --> 39:44.480
Then there is Dragon.

39:44.480 --> 39:47.480
Suddenly, Dragon cries.

39:47.480 --> 39:49.480
Oh, my stomach.

39:49.480 --> 39:51.480
We turn our heads.

39:51.480 --> 39:54.480
Dragon falls on the ground and starts rolling.

39:54.480 --> 39:56.480
Oh, chicks, help me.

39:56.480 --> 40:00.480
I've got an awful stomachache.

40:00.480 --> 40:02.480
We run to Dragon.

40:02.480 --> 40:04.480
She looks terrible.

40:04.480 --> 40:06.480
All her feathers are dirty.

40:06.480 --> 40:09.480
Her eyes are closed.

40:09.480 --> 40:13.480
Suddenly, she opens them.

40:13.480 --> 40:16.480
Oh, dear brothers and sister.

40:16.480 --> 40:20.480
Help me to get up, please, she says.

40:20.480 --> 40:22.480
We look at each other.

40:22.480 --> 40:27.480
It is the first time Dragon says please.

40:27.480 --> 40:30.480
And it is very strange.

40:30.480 --> 40:34.480
We take her by the wings and help her.

40:34.480 --> 40:36.480
Thank you, she says.

40:36.480 --> 40:40.480
Now, stand behind me, please.

40:40.480 --> 40:44.480
I'm afraid I can fall on my back.

40:44.480 --> 40:46.480
What's the matter with Dragon?

40:46.480 --> 40:49.480
Now, she says, thank you.

40:49.480 --> 40:52.480
I'm sure she is really ill.

40:52.480 --> 40:56.480
We stand behind her.

40:56.480 --> 41:00.480
Thank you, she says again.

41:00.480 --> 41:02.480
I think my stomach is okay now.

41:02.480 --> 41:06.480
One, two, three, go.

41:06.480 --> 41:09.480
She cries and starts running.

41:09.480 --> 41:11.480
We look at each other.

41:11.480 --> 41:15.480
Then we understand everything.

41:15.480 --> 41:17.480
Naughty Dragon.

41:17.480 --> 41:19.480
We start running too.

41:19.480 --> 41:23.480
Dragon turns her head and laughs.

41:23.480 --> 41:25.480
You're too silly.

41:25.480 --> 41:28.480
My brothers and sister.

41:28.480 --> 41:33.480
Suddenly, she's quiet.

41:33.480 --> 41:38.480
She stops running and sits down on the grass.

41:38.480 --> 41:42.480
Smiley and I are next to her now.

41:42.480 --> 41:44.480
We can hear a noise.

41:44.480 --> 41:46.480
Dragon is coughing.

41:46.480 --> 41:49.480
Her cough is terrible.

41:49.480 --> 41:52.480
Now, dumpty is with us too.

41:52.480 --> 41:58.480
We all hit her on the back, again and again.

41:58.480 --> 42:05.480
Suddenly, a beautiful, big butterfly flies out of her beak.

42:05.480 --> 42:09.480
Food is escaping, cries Dragon

42:09.480 --> 42:14.480
and wants to get up but starts coughing again.

42:14.480 --> 42:18.480
This time, an orange dragon fly

42:18.480 --> 42:21.480
and a purple fly come out.

42:21.480 --> 42:25.480
Then a fat grasshopper jumps out.

42:25.480 --> 42:29.480
Now, Dragon stops coughing.

42:29.480 --> 42:33.480
Again, that green animal, she cries

42:33.480 --> 42:37.480
and runs after the poor grasshopper.

42:37.480 --> 42:41.480
She keeps her mouth open when she's running, says Smiley.

42:41.480 --> 42:44.480
It's very dangerous.

42:44.480 --> 42:46.480
Yes, I say.

42:46.480 --> 42:49.480
Especially for insects.

42:56.480 --> 42:58.480
Chapter 12.

42:58.480 --> 43:01.480
A storm.

43:01.480 --> 43:03.480
It is afternoon.

43:03.480 --> 43:06.480
It is very hot.

43:06.480 --> 43:08.480
We are at home.

43:08.480 --> 43:11.480
We are hiding under Dad's wings.

43:11.480 --> 43:14.480
Mum is away.

43:14.480 --> 43:16.480
What is it?

43:16.480 --> 43:19.480
The sky isn't blue now.

43:19.480 --> 43:22.480
It is black.

43:22.480 --> 43:24.480
What's the matter?

43:24.480 --> 43:27.480
I ask Dad.

43:27.480 --> 43:31.480
There are clouds in the sky, says Dad.

43:31.480 --> 43:33.480
But why is it so dark?

43:33.480 --> 43:36.480
Ask Stunty.

43:36.480 --> 43:42.480
It's because the clouds are covering the sun and says Dad.

43:42.480 --> 43:47.480
Suddenly, we can feel the air.

43:47.480 --> 43:52.480
The air is running.

43:52.480 --> 43:56.480
Is the air afraid of the clouds, I ask Dad.

43:56.480 --> 43:59.480
Why is it running?

43:59.480 --> 44:02.480
Dad smiles and answers.

44:02.480 --> 44:06.480
The running air is the wind.

44:06.480 --> 44:14.480
I don't know why, but it's always very windy before a storm.

44:14.480 --> 44:16.480
What is a storm?

44:16.480 --> 44:19.480
Ask Smiley.

44:19.480 --> 44:21.480
She's shaking.

44:21.480 --> 44:24.480
She's afraid of the strong wind.

44:24.480 --> 44:28.480
She doesn't like the black clouds.

44:28.480 --> 44:34.480
A storm is Dad starts and stops.

44:34.480 --> 44:38.480
I can feel water on my beak.

44:38.480 --> 44:46.480
Chicks hide under my body, cries Dad, and stand next to each other.

44:46.480 --> 44:49.480
Why must I stand next to them?

44:49.480 --> 44:51.480
Ask Stragon.

44:51.480 --> 44:54.480
She doesn't want to listen to Dad.

44:54.480 --> 44:56.480
Dad is angry.

44:56.480 --> 44:58.480
Do what I say.

44:58.480 --> 45:00.480
He cries to dragon.

45:00.480 --> 45:05.480
You mustn't walk in the rain.

45:05.480 --> 45:11.480
This is only water, she says, and runs from under Dad's wing.

45:11.480 --> 45:14.480
Look.

45:14.480 --> 45:16.480
The air isn't hot now.

45:16.480 --> 45:18.480
It's cool.

45:18.480 --> 45:21.480
And the water is cool too.

45:21.480 --> 45:23.480
The rain is funny.

45:23.480 --> 45:26.480
But I must listen to Dad.

45:26.480 --> 45:28.480
So I don't go to dragon.

45:28.480 --> 45:31.480
Don't putty and smiley.

45:31.480 --> 45:33.480
Listen to Dad too.

45:33.480 --> 45:36.480
They're under his body.

45:36.480 --> 45:40.480
You are afraid of the water, cries dragon.

45:40.480 --> 45:45.480
She is dancing in the rain and laughing at us.

45:45.480 --> 45:51.480
You remember, when we go to the river, we never wet our bodies.

45:51.480 --> 45:54.480
Now dragon is all wet.

45:54.480 --> 45:56.480
Her head is wet.

45:56.480 --> 45:58.480
Her body is wet.

45:58.480 --> 46:01.480
And her wings are wet.

46:01.480 --> 46:06.480
The water is running down her beak and her legs.

46:06.480 --> 46:09.480
We can't see any feathers.

46:09.480 --> 46:12.480
Where are they?

46:12.480 --> 46:16.480
Dragon isn't dragon anymore.

46:16.480 --> 46:19.480
She's thin and ugly.

46:19.480 --> 46:23.480
Her head is very small now.

46:23.480 --> 46:28.480
She's shaking because she's laughing at us.

46:28.480 --> 46:33.480
When she laughs, we only can see her big open beak.

46:33.480 --> 46:37.480
It is so big and her neck is so thin.

46:37.480 --> 46:40.480
We close our eyes and open them again.

46:40.480 --> 46:42.480
But nothing changes.

46:42.480 --> 46:44.480
There is no dragon.

46:44.480 --> 46:48.480
Only that's ugly laughing bird.

46:48.480 --> 46:53.480
Suddenly the rain stops.

46:53.480 --> 46:57.480
But the air is still very cool.

46:57.480 --> 47:00.480
Soon our mum comes.

47:00.480 --> 47:03.480
She looks at the bird and cries.

47:03.480 --> 47:05.480
Who is that?

47:05.480 --> 47:08.480
That's dragon answers dad.

47:08.480 --> 47:13.480
Our dragon asks mum and her beak opens.

47:13.480 --> 47:17.480
Of course, ours says dad.

47:17.480 --> 47:22.480
No other ostriches have got dragons in their families.

47:23.480 --> 47:32.480
Chapter 13.

47:32.480 --> 47:35.480
Magic.

47:35.480 --> 47:39.480
We wake up and open our eyes.

47:39.480 --> 47:41.480
It is morning.

47:41.480 --> 47:45.480
It is sunny and warm again.

47:45.480 --> 47:49.480
Let's play tag, says smiley.

47:49.480 --> 47:53.480
She likes playing tag because she runs very fast.

47:53.480 --> 47:58.480
She runs faster than dragon, dumpedy and me.

47:58.480 --> 48:01.480
Okay, say dumpedy and I.

48:01.480 --> 48:04.480
We look at dragon.

48:04.480 --> 48:07.480
She's shaking again.

48:07.480 --> 48:11.480
Why are you laughing at us again, we ask.

48:11.480 --> 48:16.480
I'm not laughing at you, says a strange voice.

48:16.480 --> 48:18.480
It isn't dragon's voice.

48:18.480 --> 48:24.480
Her voice is high and loud and this voice is low and quiet.

48:24.480 --> 48:26.480
We're afraid.

48:26.480 --> 48:29.480
Who is speaking, we ask.

48:29.480 --> 48:34.480
It's me, answers the strange voice.

48:34.480 --> 48:40.480
We look around but we only can see mum, dad and dragon.

48:40.480 --> 48:43.480
Suddenly, smiley cries.

48:43.480 --> 48:45.480
It's dragon's voice.

48:45.480 --> 48:49.480
She's got a new voice.

48:49.480 --> 48:52.480
It's magic, says dumpedy.

48:52.480 --> 48:54.480
We look at dragon.

48:54.480 --> 48:56.480
She looks strange.

48:56.480 --> 49:01.480
She's shaking and her eyes are very bright.

49:01.480 --> 49:03.480
Mum, cries smiley.

49:03.480 --> 49:07.480
What's the matter with dragon?

49:07.480 --> 49:09.480
Mum comes up to dragon.

49:09.480 --> 49:14.480
She looks at her, touches her head and says dragon.

49:14.480 --> 49:16.480
You are ill.

49:16.480 --> 49:18.480
You have got a cold.

49:18.480 --> 49:20.480
You've got a high temperature.

49:20.480 --> 49:29.480
I have got a headache and a sore throat, says poor dragon and sneezes.

49:29.480 --> 49:34.480
And your nose is running, says dad.

49:34.480 --> 49:37.480
It's the rain.

49:37.480 --> 49:41.480
Rain's are very cold in Africa.

49:41.480 --> 49:44.480
You must never dance in the rain again.

49:44.480 --> 49:47.480
It's dangerous.

49:47.480 --> 49:50.480
We are sorry for dragon.

49:50.480 --> 49:56.480
She is sometimes very bad but now she is so sad.

49:56.480 --> 50:00.480
Don't be sad, dragon, says dumpedy.

50:00.480 --> 50:02.480
We like your new voice.

50:02.480 --> 50:06.480
It's so quiet.

50:06.480 --> 50:09.480
But dragon isn't happy.

50:09.480 --> 50:12.480
She starts crying.

50:12.480 --> 50:17.480
We can bring you some sweet seeds, says dumpedy.

50:17.480 --> 50:20.480
I think it's very boring to be ill.

50:20.480 --> 50:25.480
So we can stay with you all day, smile smiley.

50:25.480 --> 50:28.480
And tell you funny stories.

50:28.480 --> 50:32.480
And bring you water from the river, I say.

50:32.480 --> 50:36.480
And brush your feathers for you, smile smiley.

50:37.480 --> 50:39.480
What's the matter?

50:39.480 --> 50:42.480
Dragon looks very strange again.

50:42.480 --> 50:45.480
I can't understand why.

50:45.480 --> 50:47.480
I look and look.

50:47.480 --> 50:51.480
And suddenly I understand.

50:51.480 --> 50:54.480
Dragon is smiling.

50:54.480 --> 50:57.480
She's got a new face now.

50:57.480 --> 51:00.480
A kind, cute face.

51:00.480 --> 51:05.480
Oh, it's magic.

51:05.480 --> 51:14.480
Chapter 14.

51:14.480 --> 51:19.480
A new name.

51:19.480 --> 51:23.480
So we stay with dragon all day.

51:23.480 --> 51:28.480
Sometimes dumpedy goes and brings sweet seeds.

51:28.480 --> 51:33.480
Or I go to the river and bring some water in my beak for dragon.

51:33.480 --> 51:40.480
Smiley tells stories to her and brushes dragon's feathers.

51:40.480 --> 51:44.480
Mum stays with dragon too.

51:44.480 --> 51:52.480
She keeps her warm when dragon starts shaking and covers her from the sun.

51:52.480 --> 51:55.480
Dragon is better now.

51:55.480 --> 52:02.480
She listens to smiley, eats the seeds and drinks the water.

52:02.480 --> 52:06.480
She isn't shaking anymore.

52:06.480 --> 52:10.480
Suddenly I can hear a voice.

52:10.480 --> 52:12.480
I know this voice.

52:12.480 --> 52:14.480
I like it.

52:14.480 --> 52:18.480
It is my favorite voice.

52:18.480 --> 52:20.480
Hello.

52:20.480 --> 52:23.480
Why are you not playing today?

52:23.480 --> 52:25.480
Asks the voice.

52:25.480 --> 52:29.480
I turn round and see softy.

52:29.480 --> 52:32.480
I am very happy.

52:32.480 --> 52:36.480
And I say, because dragon is ill.

52:36.480 --> 52:40.480
Suddenly softy is very sad.

52:40.480 --> 52:43.480
I know, she says.

52:43.480 --> 52:45.480
You don't want to play with me.

52:45.480 --> 52:47.480
You don't like me.

52:47.480 --> 52:49.480
I'm going away.

52:49.480 --> 52:53.480
She turns and starts walking away.

52:53.480 --> 52:55.480
Softy, please.

52:55.480 --> 52:57.480
Don't go away, I cry.

52:57.480 --> 52:58.480
I like you.

52:58.480 --> 53:00.480
You're so nice.

53:00.480 --> 53:04.480
Why do you always run away?

53:04.480 --> 53:09.480
But, say softy, what about dragons?

53:09.480 --> 53:17.480
Why do you always talk about dragons when I want to play with you?

53:17.480 --> 53:23.480
Because dragon is our sister, I say.

53:23.480 --> 53:26.480
What?

53:26.480 --> 53:31.480
Softy's eyes become bigger than her head.

53:31.480 --> 53:32.480
Look.

53:32.480 --> 53:35.480
Here she is, I say.

53:35.480 --> 53:37.480
She's ill today.

53:37.480 --> 53:43.480
We're staying with her because it's very boring to be ill.

53:43.480 --> 53:46.480
Softy looks at dragon.

53:46.480 --> 53:51.480
Dragon isn't that old dragon anymore.

53:51.480 --> 53:53.480
She's new dragon now.

53:53.480 --> 53:57.480
She's got a kind smile.

53:57.480 --> 53:59.480
Are you dragon?

53:59.480 --> 54:02.480
Ask softy.

54:02.480 --> 54:06.480
Yes, I am, answers dragon.

54:06.480 --> 54:10.480
But dragons are ugly, angry monsters.

54:10.480 --> 54:12.480
Say softy.

54:12.480 --> 54:13.480
What?

54:13.480 --> 54:16.480
Crys dragon.

54:16.480 --> 54:20.480
We can't see her smile anymore.

54:20.480 --> 54:23.480
She's our old dragon now.

54:23.480 --> 54:28.480
I'm not an ugly, angry monster.

54:28.480 --> 54:32.480
And you are dragon, says Mum.

54:32.480 --> 54:35.480
That ostrich girl is right.

54:35.480 --> 54:40.480
Dragon means a terrible ugly monster.

54:40.480 --> 54:43.480
It likes eating other animals.

54:43.480 --> 54:47.480
It can even eat an ostrich.

54:47.480 --> 54:51.480
I think you should change your name.

54:51.480 --> 54:59.480
Oh, now I understand why you always run away, I say, to softy.

54:59.480 --> 55:02.480
Then it's true.

55:02.480 --> 55:07.480
You like me and want to play with me, smile softy.

55:07.480 --> 55:11.480
Of course, I smile at her.

55:11.480 --> 55:14.480
Dragon is very quiet now.

55:14.480 --> 55:16.480
She looks at us.

55:16.480 --> 55:18.480
She looks at Mum.

55:18.480 --> 55:21.480
And then she says,

55:21.480 --> 55:25.480
I don't want to be dragon anymore.

55:25.480 --> 55:28.480
Help me to find a nice name.

55:28.480 --> 55:32.480
We can't believe our ears.

55:32.480 --> 55:38.480
Dragon is really asking us to help her.

55:38.480 --> 55:42.480
Do you like the sun, asks Mum?

55:42.480 --> 55:44.480
Yes, I like it.

55:44.480 --> 55:51.480
It is very hot and dries us when we are wet, says dragon and coughs.

55:51.480 --> 55:54.480
Do you want to be sunny?

55:54.480 --> 55:56.480
Asks Mum.

55:56.480 --> 55:59.480
Oh, that's great, cries dragon.

55:59.480 --> 56:02.480
I like this name.

56:02.480 --> 56:05.480
Our dragon likes something.

56:05.480 --> 56:07.480
It is magic.

56:07.480 --> 56:09.480
Oh, I'm wrong.

56:09.480 --> 56:11.480
Our sister isn't dragon anymore.

56:11.480 --> 56:15.480
Now she is sunny.

56:23.480 --> 56:26.480
Chapter 15.

56:26.480 --> 56:29.480
A big day.

56:30.480 --> 56:32.480
Look at us.

56:32.480 --> 56:34.480
We're bigger now.

56:34.480 --> 56:37.480
Our legs are stronger.

56:37.480 --> 56:40.480
Dumpty is taller than Dad.

56:40.480 --> 56:44.480
And smiley is fatter than Mum.

56:44.480 --> 56:48.480
We are almost grown-ups.

56:48.480 --> 56:51.480
We don't walk with Mum and Dad anymore.

56:51.480 --> 56:56.480
We walk with other young ostriches.

56:56.480 --> 57:00.480
There are a lot of them in our group.

57:00.480 --> 57:03.480
Softy is with us too.

57:03.480 --> 57:05.480
No.

57:05.480 --> 57:08.480
She is with me.

57:08.480 --> 57:11.480
We want to be together all our life.

57:11.480 --> 57:14.480
We want to have a family.

57:14.480 --> 57:18.480
We want to have sons and daughters.

57:18.480 --> 57:23.480
I want to call my son and daughter Dumpty and smiley

57:23.480 --> 57:27.480
because I love my brother and sister.

57:27.480 --> 57:31.480
Softy has got a brother and sister too.

57:31.480 --> 57:35.480
Their names are foodie and tallie.

57:35.480 --> 57:38.480
It is because her brother likes eating.

57:38.480 --> 57:42.480
And her sister is the tallest in the family.

57:42.480 --> 57:46.480
She is even taller than her father.

57:51.480 --> 57:54.480
Two months pass.

57:54.480 --> 57:59.480
Softy and I have got a nest now.

57:59.480 --> 58:02.480
It is on the ground.

58:02.480 --> 58:05.480
There are three eggs in the nest.

58:05.480 --> 58:08.480
I guard our chicks at night.

58:08.480 --> 58:12.480
And softy does it by day.

58:12.480 --> 58:15.480
The great day comes.

58:15.480 --> 58:19.480
The first egg breaks into small pieces.

58:19.480 --> 58:22.480
And we can see our son.

58:22.480 --> 58:27.480
He has got very big feet.

58:27.480 --> 58:30.480
Our son is very clever.

58:30.480 --> 58:33.480
Laughs softy.

58:33.480 --> 58:36.480
Why? I ask.

58:36.480 --> 58:38.480
He knows our problem.

58:38.480 --> 58:39.480
Look.

58:39.480 --> 58:42.480
He has got very big feet.

58:42.480 --> 58:46.480
So his name must be footy.

58:46.480 --> 58:50.480
It is half foodie and half Dumpty.

58:50.480 --> 58:54.480
Our good boy. I smile.

58:54.480 --> 58:57.480
Here comes our daughter, say softy,

58:57.480 --> 59:00.480
when the second egg breaks.

59:00.480 --> 59:04.480
Why is she so small, I ask?

59:04.480 --> 59:07.480
I am worried.

59:07.480 --> 59:10.480
Don't worry, say softy.

59:10.480 --> 59:12.480
She must be small.

59:12.480 --> 59:15.480
Why? I ask again.

59:15.480 --> 59:18.480
Think dear, say softy.

59:18.480 --> 59:20.480
I think and think.

59:20.480 --> 59:24.480
And then I understand.

59:24.480 --> 59:28.480
It's because her name must be smally.

59:28.480 --> 59:32.480
It's half smiley and half tally.

59:32.480 --> 59:35.480
Yes, say softy.

59:35.480 --> 59:40.480
Our children are very young, but very clever.

59:40.480 --> 59:42.480
We look at the third egg.

59:42.480 --> 59:45.480
It is breaking now too.

59:45.480 --> 59:49.480
Our second daughter is coming out.

59:49.480 --> 59:52.480
She is cute.

59:52.480 --> 59:58.480
She has got yellow feathers and a long slim neck.

59:58.480 --> 01:00:03.480
Let's call her slimmy, say softy.

01:00:03.480 --> 01:00:06.480
No, say our daughter.

01:00:06.480 --> 01:00:09.480
I don't like this name.

01:00:09.480 --> 01:00:13.480
What about yellow? I ask.

01:00:13.480 --> 01:00:18.480
No, she says again.

01:00:18.480 --> 01:00:21.480
Oh, no, I cry.

01:00:21.480 --> 01:00:23.480
It's dragon.

01:00:23.480 --> 01:00:28.480
Our daughter looks at the sky and sees the sun.

01:00:28.480 --> 01:00:31.480
What is this? She asks.

01:00:31.480 --> 01:00:35.480
It's the sun answers softy.

01:00:35.480 --> 01:00:38.480
I am very quiet now.

01:00:38.480 --> 01:00:41.480
I am looking at my daughter.

01:00:41.480 --> 01:00:45.480
I can see her nice face.

01:00:45.480 --> 01:00:48.480
Of course she isn't dragon.

01:00:48.480 --> 01:00:55.480
My name is Sunny, she says, and smiles.

